<br>
Longer answer: The raid leader has the responsibility for the raid.  If you don't agree with the raid leader's strategy and are unwilling to be a part of it, then you don't belong on the raid.  Raid leaders do not have time to argue with people about each classes strategy during the raid itself.  Perhaps you can go along with the request and then speak to the raid leader after.  If you get answers you still don't like, you don't need to go on the next raid.<br>
<br>
What you didn't ask: You seem to be asking an implied question, &quot;Is the raid leader's strategy a good one&quot; -- and for that, we'd have to know the raid specifics.  There are times when I have had to focus on rods 100% -- 2 mages in a raid fight vs. Lord Inquisitor Seru for example.  If I had spent time nuking, we would not have won the fight.  There are times when rods didn't matter much at all -- 7 mages in a raid fight vs. Rumblecrush. <p><img src="http://www.ballio.com/lineup.gif">
