Raid leader telling me *not* to nuke or use pet even if I know there is no reason not to?  He wouldn't have to ask me to leave, I would gate anyways.  Go find a rod bot.<br>
<br>
I think many here are missing the point of this survey.  The issue is not about refusing to summon rods, but being told to *ONLY* summon rods and do *nothing* else.<br>
<br>
I know what needs to be done on raids and when I can or must nuke/pet/rod.  Most experienced mages do. Having a raid leader say this is like a raid leader saying, &quot;Paladin, you are only to use your sword, but don't use any of your spells, or bash, or taunt, or LoH, even if you know it would help&quot;.  Silly, no?<br>
<br>
The best Raid Leaders trust the individual classes present to actually know their jobs with minimum direction.  Micro-managing raid leaders who tell everyone exactly what to do and when to do it usually have lousy raid attendance and success rates.<br>
<br>
My guild practically worships its mages for the rod production they provide.  I smile when I get a tell  from somebody asking, &quot;Is it ok if I grab one of those rods on the ground now?&quot; There is no &quot;Gimme Rods!&quot;.  They accept &quot;No&quot; as an answer for a rod request, since they trust me to be on the ball and know when rods are needed. This is how it should be.  Respect and appreciate my mana, and I'm happy to assist.  Treat me like nothing but a rod-whore and I'll /cast8 Gate.<br>
<br>
Access to my Rods is a PRIVILEDGE, not a RIGHT.  Don't agree, find another mage.  If some RL wants to boot me for that, I'm fine with that.  They just got weaker.<br>
<br>
Sage Finraziel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufumelin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fumelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 9:13:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: SURVEY II: Do you think it is appropriate for the...</span><hr size=1> &lt;nm&gt; potentially flamable material removed<br>
